{"id":466004172,"lang":"python3","time":"4Â months","timestamp":1615379980,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"52 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/466004172/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Integer to Roman","memory":"14.3 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def intToRoman(self, num: int) -> str:\n        divs = [1000, 100, 10, 1]\n        div2symbols = {1000: ['M', 'M', 'M'], 100: ['M', 'D', 'C'], 10: ['C', 'L', 'X'], 1: ['X', 'V', 'I']}\n        output = []\n        for d in divs:\n            q = num // d\n            o_symbol = div2symbols[d][2]\n            f_symbol = div2symbols[d][1]\n            t_symbol = div2symbols[d][0]\n            if 1 <= q <= 3:\n                output.append(o_symbol * q)\n            elif q == 4:\n                output.append(o_symbol + f_symbol)\n            elif 5 <= q <= 8:\n                output.append(f_symbol + (o_symbol) * (q - 5))\n            elif q == 9:\n                output.append(o_symbol + t_symbol)\n            num = num % d\n\n        return ''.join(output)\n\n                \n\n\n\n        \n\n\n        ","compare_result":"","title_slug":"integer-to-roman"}
